name: Casa Madrona - Urban Oasis, 1 block from the Park!
summary: Gorgeous, architect remodeled, 1917 Dutch Colonial in the heart of Madrona. 2 blocks to restaurants and shops, and library. 1 block to playground and park, with doggy play area. 10 mins to Lake WA beaches, trails and Marina. 3 mins to Cap Hill.  4 Bedroom, 2.5 bath, Chef's Kitchen, gracious living and dining room, enclosed back garden, deck, grill, fruit trees. Off street parking. We are flexible with the bedrooms. Kid's toys, books and swing chair!
space: Casa Madrona is a gorgeous, architect remodeled, 1917 Dutch Colonial in the heart of Madrona. This beautiful, gracious home has been completely restored from the studs up, adding period touches such as window benches and floor to ceiling bookshelves. The house is perfect for family gatherings, large or small, groups of friends, or colleagues.  Upstairs are 4 bedrooms and two full baths with Olympic mountain and city skyline views. The main floor features a formal entry leading to a sun-lit living room with cozy gas fireplace, and lots of books, couches and window seat for cozy relaxing. French doors lead to a spacious, sunny dining room and a huge, open, fully stocked Chef's kitchen with enormous island and even a little cookbook nook. The dining room leads to a large cedar deck and a fully fenced back yard with scrumptious apples in the Autumn, and raspberries and herbs in the summer.  The basement has a top of the line, large-sized washer/dryer. There is an attached 1 car garage and

host_about: We are a family who love travel and adventure! We have stayed in many vacation rentals over the years, and lived abroad as well, in London. We feel like we really know what makes a great home away from home. We welcome guests from all walks of life and every culture. We live next door and enjoy getting to know our guests if we have common ground. We are available whenever you need us. We have a lively four year old daughter, so if you have kids, we can recommend  a lot of activities and have extra toys to share, including a trampoline in our backyard next door. We have had vacation rentals on and off for ten years so we truly understand the needs of families, groups, wedding parties, etc... we will do everything we can to facilitate a wonderful stay at Casa Madrona.

name: Sunrise in Seattle Master Suite
summary: This property is located in the lovely Maple Leaf neighborhood. We are right on an arterial which will take you downtown in approximately 15 minutes. We are walking distance from several coffee shops, restaurants and bars, and a short drive from several grocery and convenience stores. Don't miss out on a trip to the local park, Maple Leaf Reservoir Park, complete with a play ground, a running track, pickle ball court and a view of downtown and the stunning mountain ranges of WA!
space: Located in Seattle, this is a spacious, clean and very comfortable "home away from home" for traveling business professionals, visitors to Seattle for a short-term stay and is ideal for a single person or a couple. The private room & private bath is furnished with: - Queen-sized bed with clean and high-end linens - Small refrigerator - Microwave and dishes - Television, cable, DVD & WiFi - Desk & chair - Large closet - Use of hot & cold water cooler and washer/dryer - Your private bathroom is attached to suite  The location yields very easy access to I-5, 8-10 minutes from downtown Seattle and 5 miles from The University of Washington. Within walking distance of shopping/restaurants, a metro bus stop and a short drive to access SR- 520 and I-90. This room/bath is comparable to a spacious & comfortable hotel room rather than a shared living situation. Each day, any dishes you use can be set on a tray directly outside of your room and will be promptly replaced with clean dishes. No smoki

interaction: We do not live on the property, however we do have a property manager who lives upstairs and we are available via email or phone if you need anything during your stay!
house_rules: We ask that you please use nearby street parking, but there is plenty of it so you won't have to go far!
host_about: We're a former Seattle couple who just couldn't bring ourselves to let go of our beautiful home.  We know Seattle, we love Seattle, we grew up here.  We just couldn't take the rain and traffic year round anymore.  What to do?  Turn it into an AirBNB dream of course!  For nearly a decade now we've been staying at our house when we're in town and when we're away.... we love to share it with the AirBNB Community.  Comfort, communication and kindness are our highest values.  We really care about what we are doing here.  We don't run multiple places. We're always available via phone or email even when we're traveling but most of the time, our house manager Kevin keeps everything on track.   This is our beloved home.  Our neighborhood.  Our memories.  We love hosting guests.  We love helping travelers make special memories of their own in our Seattle home. When we travel we prefer our hosts to be avilable if needed but otherwise not be around much which is how we run our place.  Our main motto in life is "Love others as you'd want to be loved.  To treat others as we'd want to be treated"

name: Cozy Studio, min. to downtown -WiFi
summary: The Cozy Studio is a perfect launchpad for your city getaway. Enjoy amenities such as WiFi, Queen sized bed, a mini-fridge, microwave, coffee maker, iron, hair dryer, and more. Close to bus lines that go into downtown and the airport. For more information, see entire listing.
space: Hello fellow travelers, Save some money and have a great time in Seattle! Rent this comfortable studio (private suite), furnished room with a queen bed, a 3/4 bathroom with large shower, a very basic kitchenette and a private entrance. This studio is on the first floor of my townhouse. The room faces east towards the street. The studio gets plenty of natural light and is furnished with noise reducing curtains and blinds that help reduce outside noise. The studio is also equipped with a noise machine. Free WiFi is available. Please feel free to ask questions, I look forward to hearing from you.

name: Fab, private seattle urban cottage!
space: Soo centrally located, this is a little house  all your own ! This cozy,charming cottage for two has cathedral ceilings,skylight, and a french door overlooking the garden. We just redecorated for a mid-century  vibe ! Tho' only 23x10 ,it has wifi,tv,dvd,and ipod  stereo or laptop (URL HIDDEN) addition to the queen bed, small foam futon available for autonomous sleeping!.We try to provide for all your needs.The bath is newly remodeled w/ wet room, (kitchenette has a sink micro,toaster-oven ,Nespresso machine ( well, it is Seattle ,aka coffee town  !) and a half size fridge. You are ready for coffee,tea, a light breakfast and for takeout!!    Somehow ,it is 15 minutes to everywhere, downtown,ballard, capital hill..even closer to south lake union..The university district 1.5  mile away,fremont even closer! Downtown , 2 mi.,wallingfords shopping, movies and 15 + restaurants 5 blocks.    Our walk-ability score is 94, buses on corner, bikes available,yes,there is easy free street parking too

notes: Check in is at three, if you'd like a snack or a bit of the neighborhood..  If I can help as a local resource, let me know.  I recommend Archie Mcfee's for joke gifts for all occasions! ... and Tutti Bella is fab pizza both blocks away 44 n stone, 45th and stone.  There is always Gasworks park and the essential bakery for lunch ,34( both are walkable from the house) and woodlawn.

house_rules: Please treat the cottage as if it were your own, comfortably and carefully.  Energy conservative habits expected please. Rinse and crush recycling and check the list of what is recycled, in seattle it is long. Quiet before 9am, and after 10 pm, it's good for us all!.  Please no smoking or loud parties, be conscious of others .    HOT TUB: unfortunately,hot tubs are delicate flowers and break far too frequently.( almost ready to give up) please do not book for the hot tub, just in case. Hours 9am-9 pm. please rinse off in the shower first.Please keep your visit to 20 minutes in consideration of others who may use.The hot tub will accommodates $400 lbs. Only 2 folks in the hot tub at a time, sorry no outside guests.Please be Quiet after 9, as the neighbors children sleep  12 ft. away.please wear a suit! Hot tub off to conserve energy nov15 -march 15.

name: Glorious sun room w/ memory foambed
summary: This beautiful double room features a magical sleeping room and a second room that features a sitting area and breakfast /mini kitchen area. On two major bus lines, come enjoy the burgeoning arts district just minutes away from downtown Seattle
space: Our new Sunny space has a private room from the 1904 vintage era. This building has a VERY interesting history and features comfortable rooms with lovely wood floors and wainscotting down the hallways. Restored with antiques and your very own private room and a shared  AMAZING large (think mexican tiled heaven with 6 showerheads) tiled bathroom that is shared only with the other air bandb room.. Our new space is surrounded by art and creative studios with our resident Jack Russell wandering around to say hello occasionally. Dog is kept out of the guest rooms but they do walk around with me so most likely not a good fit for the super allergic. You will have full access to our kitchen and it's cooking facilities.Your room is your  own private sunny space. Although your room is private you share the building with the owner and her own art studio and artists from diverse back grounds who are very respectful of all guests. This space is lovely and fairly quiet but don't expect crickets sing

neighborhood_overview: Lots of restaurants (see our guide book) bars,coffee shops and antique /eclectic stores. We also have a huge parking lot and busses right across the street. This neighborhood is still a tiny bit gritty but is honestly more sparkly than a few years ago. Come see it for yourself Industrial Arts district meets thriving commercial meets victorian era esthetics A little grit,a lot of love and a burgeoning arts community. Easy 15 minute bus ride to Pike Place Market,the Big Wheel and Seattle Center and transportation to points beyond like Ballard locks,university district and Bellevue
notes: This area is an arts district,you will see all types of people so be open to enjoying the scenery and have an adventure
transit: Car 2 go is in this neigborhood Bus is across the street to downtown (14 minutes) and two major freeways (exit 162 off of Interstate 5 and "car to go" service is  right outside our door most days Bus 124 and 106 are right across the street that goes right to downtown to light link rail and the airport. We also have an easily walkable neighborhood Here are instructions from the airport if you are using mass transit Yes you will get the link rail from the airport to the underground tunnel, get off in the international district, cross the tracks to go to bus number 106 going south to Georgetown. The bus will take about 15 minutes. You will get off in Georgtown at the Doris street stop. Call me from there , you will walk back towards city 1/2 block. Our building is located in the middle of the block. I am happy to answer any ?'s before and during your visit
access: 24 /7 access kitchen, bathroom and community space wifi access
interaction: I have a hands on warm approach to guests but also give them their own space to relax and enjoy our space
house_rules: No drugs,no smoking inside *outside in front of the building is fine though, damage deposit of $150  for guests with children (refunded if no damage ) and may be waived if reviews speak about them. You are welcome to cook  in kitchen encouraged but please clean up after yourself. Please do not have guests who are not registered through airbandb unless okd by host.  ***Late arrivals (after 6pm) - please arrange before booking , I am willing to work with you if your arrival is at a reasonable time*** Please be respectful of quit hours from 11-8am and keep conversations,music and sounds at a low volume for others to sleep .  Also special note even tho Mary Jane is legal now the host is allergic to it so please ask about the smoking area if you would like to partake of that special little weed. Thank you
host_about: I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a Non profit community  Arts and Cultural Center. I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs when needed (this includes you) spend time with friends and my dogs.  The guest rooms are located in the Centers lovely  1904 building and we share the building with professional artist studios (mine included). The building is truly a vintage charmer and I have been doing the renovations myself. I think you will enjoy my handy work. Special things to be aware of***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunatly are not ADA accesible. ***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a coffee shop that on the weekends sometimes has fun shows / music / drag shows/mystery theater..which is fun for most but light sleepers may not be ok with this activity.  I look forward to meeting you. I have two small calm Jack Russel's who may greet you but do not  stay in the space at night. I enjoy animals,art, gardening and people.. . This is not a hotel and I do not have staff so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) and communicate this BEFORE your arrival as I arrange my day around meeting you. Late arrivals may be possible with prior arrangement and may be handled by our night manager Rick. I am an easy going person band always try to keep our space mellow  NO SMOKING IN BUILDING / NO VAPING/ NO POT ‰Û_you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every visitor a friend but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dogs.I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I even have a lonely planet guide to Seattle if you want to borrow it.I cant wait to meet you!To earn more about our area (Georgetown) follow (copy and paste) this link (Website hidden by Airbnb) My life motto"Life is short, art is long"

name: Downtown/Convention Ctr B&B - Nice!
summary: Great location, 98% walk score, next to the Convention Center, includes snacks, WiFi, free street parking, washer/dryer.  Read the reviews and you'll know I do everything I can to exceed guests' expectations. Rates from $99 to $219 -- like hotels, depending on season or special events.
space: Greetings from Seattle. Thanks for considering my place. I've worked to make this the best Airbnb deal in downtown Seattle -- no deposit required, no "check-out checklist" to clean, change linens or do laundry before leaving -- you just leave when you're ready and Nadia, the world's best housekeeper, will take care of everything.  The calendar is always up to date, so if you're Airbnb-verified, you can book immediately with Instant Booking.  Otherwise, drop me a note and let me know a little about yourself and why you're coming to Seattle. Here's more... This is a private bedroom and private bathroom in a condo, just off Pike Street.  An ideal hotel alternative:  the best in comfort, price, and location -- a half block east of the Central Business District that includes the Convention Center, a 7-minute walk from the Westlake Light Rail link to/from the airport, a block south of the Pike Pine Corridor which encompasses the Retail Shopping Core, and a block west of Capitol Hill, Seattle

notes: Free Zone 21 Parking.  There are 60 blocks in a 10 x 7-block radius of the building for free Zone 21 parking.  If you can't find parking on the street right in front of the building when you arrive, you might want to take your luggage up to the condo before looking for a space.  The parking permit will be on the desk in your room, along with a map showing all Zone 21 parking spaces.  Once parked, you can stay there for 72 hours before you need to move your car to another Zone 21 space. Parking is on a first-come, first-served basis, but since I moved here in 1998, I've usually been able to find a space within a couple blocks of the building, but on certain times, like Saturday nights and Sundays, I've had to venture further out in the neighborhood.  With a little (sometimes a lot) of patience, I've never had to resort to parking in a pay lot. transit: On a map it looks like the building is right next to the freeway, but the freeway goes under the convention center, so it's easy to walk anywhere downtown.
access: In the email I send you before your arrival, it'll tell you how to gain access to the building and apartment.  It's easy and there are no restrictions on the time of day or night you arrive, come and go, or check out. On a map it looks like the condo is next to a freeway, but it runs under the city, so it's easy to walk anywhere downtown.
house_rules: Dear Prospective Guest,   There aren‰Ûªt really many house rules.  Basically, come in and make yourself at home.  There‰Ûªs no such thing as a check-in time that‰Ûªs too late, so no worries there.  Let me know if you'd like an earlier check-in time than 3pm or later check-out time than noon.  It can usually be arranged, depending on other bookings.  Worst case scenario, we can store your luggage. All the food and drinks in your private little food alcove are complimentary, so help yourself to what's been called The World‰Ûªs First Free Mini Bar.   The building is concrete, which means it‰Ûªs pretty soundproof, so you don‰Ûªt need to be shy about the volume of music or TV ‰ÛÒ just keep it moderate after 10pm.   Hold onto the keys and, if you drive, return the parking permit when you check out.  The lobby key fob has a $50 replacement cost imposed by the homeowners association that I must pass on to you, should you lose it.  With that in mind, no one has ever lost one in 16 years, so I‰Ûªm pretty confid
host_about: I moved to Seattle in 1990 and love it here.  Beautiful city, wonderful people.  I've been hosting since 1999 and have met terrific people from all over the world.  It's gratifying to be able to provide an affordable, comfortable hotel alternative right in the heart of the City.I'm also a writer and nutritional therapist.  I love my work.

name: The Adorable Sweet Orange Craftsman
summary: The Sweet Orange is a delightful and spacious 2 BR/1BA home with urban views of the mountains and sound.  Classic charm and super comfy, all in a fantastic location!  In a lovely neighborhood only 3 blocks from center of the West Seattle Junction!
space: The Sweet Orange invites you to stay and play, in West Seattle's best neighborhood: The Junction.   This ultra cool and colorful turn of the century home is tastefully and comfortably furnished.  It is 1200 sq ft, with 2 bedrooms (king & queen), 1 full bath , a well-equipped kitchen, living and dining area.  There is a pull-out twin sofa in the sun room, off the master bedroom.  The main living area has hardwood floors with large area rugs and a cozy gas fireplace.  There are rich colors and textures throughout.  Amenities include 2 flat screen TV's, DVD, DVR, WIFI, dishwasher, and a Stok charcoal grill.  Greet the sun with your morning coffee on the grand front porch, and enjoy your NW wines on the sunny back deck!  There is an urban view to the West from inside and out, including the Puget Sound and Olympic mountains!   The home is on a quiet residential street, yet  located in the heart of The Junction.  It is 2 walkable blocks from plentiful retail shops, restaurants, coffeehouses,

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is awesome!  Just far enough away to be quiet and residential, yet only a SHORT walk to tons of fun shops and restaurants, and local flavor.  The best of both.    Be on the beach, on a ferry or on an 18 hole golf course in minutes!
notes: The house is super clean and well-equipped.  The Sweet Orange enjoys guests who are gentle on the quality furnishings and considerate of the quiet neighborhood.  Welcome...if that's your speed!
transit: The Metro bus transit center and downtown water taxi shuttle are right here, in the Junction.  Downtown is a snap, by water taxi, bus or car.  The stadiums are right across the bridge and the airport is 20 mins away.
access: Guests enjoy a private front yard garden and a sunny view deck overlooking the gardens below.  In the side yard is your personal charcoal BBQ.  There is a common laundry room on the lower level, with private access.  Parking is on the street, in front of the house.
interaction: Cassie waters and gardens periodically, so if you wish to connect and visit, that is always a welcome option, if she is in town.  If privacy is your thing, no need to worry.
house_rules: *The Sweet Orange is a No Smoking house.  The Sweet Orange does not host parties and provides only for overnight guests listed on the contract.  *Quiet hours are from 10pm-8am, and noise consideration for guests in the MIL, on the lower level, is requested.   *Young children are welcomed on a case-by-case basis, for suitability for the property. *The Sweet Orange is committed to the earth and requests your cooperation with recycling and composting, which is required in the city of Seattle.  .   *The City allows for only two overnight resident vehicles per household, for on-street parking.      *Small dogs are welcome on a case by case basis, and there is up to a $100/per pet fee for pet guests.  Uninvited pet guests will forfeit the entire damage deposit.
host_about: The Sweet Orange reflects my passion and zest for life:  colorful, creative self expression;  well-cared for and clean;  lovable and loved!    I am forever tweaking, improving, learning and expanding in my creative endeavors and personal growth.  Things I love:  The gardens at The Sweet Orange, and The Tangerine Dream, are my ever-evolving work in progress.  When I am designing, time stands still!  I am a world traveler and frequently on the go.  Dogs and kitty's!  My beloved Chessie, makes my heart sing!  Food and wine, for goodness sake.  I cherish good health and am a steward for a healthy planet.I invite guests who travel as I do, with respect and regard for the gifts each place has to offer.  I welcome connection, as well as respect privacy.   Enjoy life and savor the color Orange!

name: The Coolest Tangerine Dream MIL!
summary: Welcome to my delicious Tangerine Dream!  A colorful and cozy 900 sq ft 2BR/1BA mother-in-law apartment, in the heart of the West Seattle Junction.  Located on the lower level of a Craftsman home, enjoy a spacious open floor plan, surrounded by beautiful tile mosaics and fabulous colors.  Open your french doors into a sweet backyard garden or   cozy up to a warm gas fireplace.  Ready to adventure out?  You can walk to cool shops and eateries, or grab rapid transit to downtown or the water taxi!
space: The Tangerine Dream is a delightful, cozy mother-in-law apartment below The Adorable Sweet Orange Craftsman. This artistic haven occupies 900 sq ft  with 2 bedrooms (queens) and 1 full bath, in an open floor plan.  The two bedrooms are at opposite ends of the apartment from each other, and have large custom fabric doorways.  The Tangerine was carefully designed and built for nesting in a creative space, while you cozy up to a sweet, gas fireplace in the corner of the living room. Rich colors, mosaic tile patterns, terracotta floors with large area rugs, delight the artist in you and invite you to relax.  Enjoy a movie on your flat screen HDTV or access WiFi anywhere, inside and out.    When the sun beckons you, throw open your french doors to a bright and colorful backyard garden, with privacy fencing and trellises. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is the best of two worlds...walkably close to tons of fun  AND peaceful and quiet.  A car is not essential, as walkability and local transit are very reliable.
notes: The Tangerine Dream welcomes guests who are considerate and respectful of all the care and love that have gone into creating this special place.  Wild ones or loud night owls will be a better fit somewhere else.  There are quieter hours from 10pm-8am.  The Sweet Orange occupies the main floor.  Please bring your happy vibe and take good care of my house, and you will have a great time!
transit: The local Metro bus transit center is four minutes away, on foot.  From there, be in downtown in 15 minutes, on the Rapid Ride bus (outside of rush hour, of course).  There is also a free shuttle to the Downtown Water Taxi, located here.
access: The Tangerine Dream has a private, ground level entrance and deck,  a dedicated parking space, secure access to shared laundry room, and enjoyment of the fenced backyard garden.
interaction: I take my cues of guest interaction from my guests.  For longer terms, I usually show the guests around, when they arrive.  For quick visits, we make arrangements for obtaining the keys.  From time to time, I come around and tend to the garden, so can make arrangements with guests to do this at a time that best suits.  I welcome guest contact for anything that comes up (I live 2 miles away), and I am respectful of a guests desire for privacy.  I value and practice good communication!

Recycling and composting is required by Seattle City ordinance, so we require your compliance.

notes: you may want to unload from the alley, as the house is above street level with  10 stairs.
access: all of this space is yours! There is a large garden room with outdoor couch and chairs in the front of the house.
interaction: Often in the summer I am away at my yurt! you can always text with questions, and if urgent I can be there in an hour and a half.   Please note that this apartment is underneath the main house and best suited for quiet folks. ( upstairs, likewise.)
house_rules: Please treat the apartment as if it were your own, comfortably and carefully. You may unload if desired on the alley just beyond the orange cottage if you'd like, but please park in front of house , on street.  Energy conservative habits expected please. Rinse and crush recycling and check the list of what is recycled, in seattle it is long. ( and we are fined if too many recyclaables are found in trash. Trash is through back yard, on alley. Quiet before 9am, and after 10 pm, it's good for us all!. Dogs are welcome with $75 non refundable rug cleaning fee.( sorry but all blankets and rugs must be washed as some are allergic.) Please no smoking or loud parties, be conscious of others .     please empty trash and recycling, strip sheets off beds before leaving.This allows later check out.
host_about: I am a therapist/innkeeper.I know my city well and am know as a fab concierge. I love art, the outdoors, books, music and dogs.  fav activities? thrifting, museums, spending time at my yurt.

name: Luna Park Lower - West Seattle
summary: You couldn't ask for a more convenient location!  Our two-bedroom home is nestled in a quiet neighborhood at the north end of beautiful West Seattle.  Walk 1/2-block up the street for a spectacular panoramic view of the moon over Elliot Bay.
space: This 1920's home is a classic gem.  Two bedrooms, each with a queen bed, allow Luna Park Lower to sleep up to four guests.  There is a spacious living room which features a fireplace and soaring coved ceilings.  A fully equipped kitchen with breakfast nook, dining room, and full bathroom complete the space.  Towels and linens are provided, as well as basic kitchen gear, coffee, wireless high-speed internet, and satellite tv.   A portable crib is available upon request.  Luna Park Lower is a pet-free property.     Luna Park Lower occupies the main floor of this shared house.  The second floor, Luna Park Upper, is a completely separate vacation rental with its own entrance.  There is a washer and dryer available in the basement that you may use during your stay, and a charcoal grill in the yard during summer months.  The yard and basement are shared by all guests.   It is usually easy to find a parking spot on the street near the house (free parking, no permit required).  Our small drive

host_about: Laura & Joe Ross - Having both owned houses before we married in February of 2009, we decided to try the vacation rental business rather than sell either.  Our first guests were Laura's family, in town for the wedding.  Since then, with Joe's work as a musician and dancer and our joint project of raising three kids, we are plenty busy!  However, we take pride in putting our visitors first and have really enjoyed meeting our guests and sharing the city we love with them.

name: Stay here for a blast!!!!
summary: Great location in West Seattle. Freshly painted, fully furnished with common areas and bedroom.  Take a 10 minute bus ride to downtown. Plenty of room for parking. One bedroom is available in this beautiful brick home with large bathroom.
space: Great location in West Seattle, fully furnished common areas and bedroom to rent for: $40/ night 5 nights minimum.     $258/ week.     $840/ month.  Take a 10 minute bus ride to down town plenty of room for parking. One bedroom is available in this beautiful brick home with large back yard and deck for cook outs. The roommate ages range from 28 to 50.  My wife Cassandra and I are occasionally over to take care of the place.  Feel free to ask us any questions.  The house is very quite, everybody is busy working or they relax in their bedrooms. We tend to have a get together about once a month and I encourage everyone to hang out in the common area but its not necessary. I enjoy the mountains and tend to get out hiking, skiing or snowmobiling as much as possible and would encourage you to join me. I am available for a small fee and advanced notice for guide or shuttle service Feel free to contact me with questions at (phone number hidden)  Thanks,  Mike Collins

name: Upscale Seattle Hotel Alternative
summary: This property is located in the lovely Maple Leaf neighborhood. We are right on an arterial which will take you downtown in approximately 15 minutes. We are walking distance from several coffee shops, restaurants and bars, and a short drive from several grocery and convenience stores. Don't miss out on a trip to the local park, Maple Leaf Reservoir Park, complete with a play ground, a running track, pickle ball court and a view of downtown and the stunning mountain ranges of WA!
space: Located in Seattle, this is a cozy, clean and very comfortable "home away from home" for traveling business professionals, visitors to Seattle for a short-term stay and is ideal for a single person or a couple. The private room & private bath is furnished with: - Queen-sized bed with clean and high-end linens - Small refrigerator - Microwave - Television, cable, DVD & WiFi - Desk & chair - Sink & mirror in the room in addition to the bath sink - Large closet - Use of hot & cold water cooler and washer/dryer - Directly adjacent to your private bathroom The location yields very easy access to I-5, 8-10 minutes from downtown Seattle and 5 miles from The University of Washington.   Within walking distance of shopping/restaurants and a short drive to access   SR- 520 and I-90. This room/bath is comparable to a cozy & comfortable hotel room rather than a shared living situation. interaction: We do not live on the property, however we do have a property manager who lives upstairs and we are available via email or phone if you need anything during your stay!
house_rules: We ask that you please use nearby street parking, but there is plenty of it so you won't have to go far!
host_about: We're a former Seattle couple who just couldn't bring ourselves to let go of our beautiful home.  We know Seattle, we love Seattle, we grew up here.  We just couldn't take the rain and traffic year round anymore.  What to do?  Turn it into an AirBNB dream of course!  For nearly a decade now we've been staying at our house when we're in town and when we're away.... we love to share it with the AirBNB Community.  Comfort, communication and kindness are our highest values.  We really care about what we are doing here.  We don't run multiple places. We're always available via phone or email even when we're traveling but most of the time, our house manager Kevin keeps everything on track.   This is our beloved home.  Our neighborhood.  Our memories.  We love hosting guests.  We love helping travelers make special memories of their own in our Seattle home. When we travel we prefer our hosts to be avilable if needed but otherwise not be around much which is how we run our place.  Our main motto in life is "Love others as you'd want to be loved.  To treat others as we'd want to be treated"

interaction: We do not live on the property, however we do have a property manager who lives upstairs and we are available via email or phone if you need anything during your stay!
house_rules: We ask that you use nearby street parking, but there is plenty of it so you won't have to go far!
host_about: We're a former Seattle couple who just couldn't bring ourselves to let go of our beautiful home.  We know Seattle, we love Seattle, we grew up here.  We just couldn't take the rain and traffic year round anymore.  What to do?  Turn it into an AirBNB dream of course!  For nearly a decade now we've been staying at our house when we're in town and when we're away.... we love to share it with the AirBNB Community.  Comfort, communication and kindness are our highest values.  We really care about what we are doing here.  We don't run multiple places. We're always available via phone or email even when we're traveling but most of the time, our house manager Kevin keeps everything on track.   This is our beloved home.  Our neighborhood.  Our memories.  We love hosting guests.  We love helping travelers make special memories of their own in our Seattle home. When we travel we prefer our hosts to be avilable if needed but otherwise not be around much which is how we run our place.  Our main motto in life is "Love others as you'd want to be loved.  To treat others as we'd want to be treated"

name: Artsy Green Lake Guest Room with Active Family
summary: Our home in Green Lake is smack in the middle of Seattle's north end, an ideal spot for travelers and commuters. It's surrounded by fabulous parks, lovely old homes and tons of urban amenities.  We have two very young children who love people of all ages, so our home is nearly always full of activity and sound. We enjoy welcoming guests into our fold, so we prefer longer stays so that we have a chance to get to know folks. ** Please note: Our Guest room is only available til June 15, 2018. **
space: Our 1909 Craftsman style house is in a great walking neighborhood, just a block and a half from Green Lake. Our place has an open floor plan, high ceilings, hardwood floors, lots of windows, and lots of light. We enjoy our home and enjoy sharing it with friends and guests. If you're interested in staying with us, please drop us a line. Let us know a bit about yourself as well as the dates you'd like to stay. We look forward to hearing from you!

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood has tons of conveniences: a great breakfast spot on the corner (voted Best Breakfast in Seattle), several pubs and coffee shops w/in a two block radius (with excellent food, beer, wine and coffee selections. . . sometimes all at the same cafe). We are a seven minute walk to PCC Natural Markets (our closest grocery store). Shops, yoga studios, doctor's offices, and more are minutes away by foot.  Best of all‰Û_ there‰Ûªs easy access to nature. We‰Ûªre just two blocks to Green Lake, home to Seattle's most popular running trail as well as a wide variety of birds (including great blue herons and bald eagles). We‰Ûªre also just minutes away from Ravenna and Cowen Park, a wooded ravine filled with ferns and evergreen trees where you can travel the walking paths / running trails, listen to bird calls or the bubbling of the stream, and forget you are in the city.
notes: The house has one bathroom: The house's inhabitants (and all of our bladders) are happiest and most harmonious when showers are quick (or when we give each other a heads up before taking a long, luxurious bath in our big old clawfoot tub). You'll know you're staying with kids. Our sons love interacting with guests: They'll be eager to get to know you, chatter with you, and play with you. If you are at home during the day, you will be surrounded by toys‰Û_ on your way to the kitchen, to the bathroom, to the dining room table. Toys are part of our world. You'll know you are staying with a family. There will be play dates with loud laughter, running, shrieking and music playing (think toy whistles and keyboards that play nursery rhymes, the joy). There will be grown ups and kids goofing around and wrestling on the living room rug, and grown ups hollering at kids to get a move on so we can get out the door. You'll hear it all. And we try to keep a tidy house, but you'll know you're living wi
transit: With so many places within walking distance, it‰Ûªs easy to live here without a car. We‰Ûªre on several major bus routes. Bike paths are everywhere. There's even a bus on the corner that will take Microsoft employees directly to their main campus, making it easy to be car-free even when a job is on the other side of Lake Washington. There is free on-street parking.  Our place has super easy access to I-5 and is a short drive to SR-520 and I-90 where you can travel to the east side (Microsoft, T-Mobile, etc).   We're a short bus or bike ride away from the UW (University of Washington), minutes from Capitol Hill, Fremont or downtown, a few blocks away from the PCC (food co-op) and exactly half a mile from Whole Foods Market.  Nearby buses include the 16, 26, and 48.
access: The guest room is on the main floor of the house, right off the dining room in the heart of the home. It's furnished simply and comfortably. The room has a closet, a full-size bed, nightstand, desk and chair, and a dresser. We have free WiFi, and we're a non-smoking household.
interaction: Your hosts are a pretty down-to-earth Lesbian couple in our 40s and our two sons, ages 3 and 6 years old (who typically greet guests excitedly when they come home). We also have an indoor-only cat and a quiet, silly, small dog. I have a great evening job as a community college ESL instructor. My wife works days as an architectural designer. Our boys will be eager to welcome you into our family while you're here, so a love of kids is a must. You'd share the common areas of the house with us.  There is a shared bathroom, a kitchen with a gas stove, and a washer/dryer in the basement (where there is also room for bike storage). We're pretty mellow, yet we enjoy being social and host occasional dinner parties. If we have one while you're here, we hope you'll stick around and meet some great new people! We also like to enjoy rainy afternoons at home, reading, relaxing, cooking, and playing with our sons.
house_rules: While staying with us, we welcome you to spend as much or as little time as you prefer engaging with our family. Because you‰Ûªll be spending a lot of time with us and around our young ones, we require: All guests must have government issued ID on file with Airbnb. We will check and scan ID upon check in. A few other notes: SAFETY/SECURITY: We live in a safe neighborhood, but one that has its share of property crime. Doors and windows need to be closed and locked before leaving the house. The basement/laundry room needs to be kept locked. If you use a heater or a fan in your room, please turn these off before leaving, too.  BATHROOM:  The shower curtain should be on the INSIDE of the tub before showering so that the floor and walls remain dry during/after the shower. Not everyone is used to claw foot tubs, so please ask if you have any questions. The drain/lint screen should be cleaned out after each shower. COMPUTER USE: We minimize screen time at our house, so we ask that if you watch
host_about: We're an eco-friendly Lesbian couple in our early 40s: a community college instructor and an architectural designer.  We love to garden, bike, travel locally and visit friends. We have two young children who enjoy interacting with guests and helping welcome them into our (ever-expanding extended) family.

name: Newly Remodeled "Boho Modern" in Mapleleaf
summary: This stunning apartment was completely remodeled in 2018.  Offering a light bright contemporary style you won't find anywhere else it's a place you're going to love coming home to (especially when it's grey outside).  Located in North East Seattle in the charming Maple leaf Neighborhood, we are right on an arterial which will take you downtown in approximately 15 minutes. We are walking distance from  a number of chic coffee shops, restaurants and bars, and a short drive from grocery stores.
space: After hosting Airbnb guests for nearly a decade, in late 2017 owners Joey and Jessica began working with local designer Rose Johnson to completely rethink their Mother-In-Law apartment.  With Rose's vision guiding through out, this newly remodeled masterpiece debuted in the spring of 2018.   The space they've created offers a truly unique and relaxing Seattle experience.      Throughout this spacious flat every color and texture.... every object and piece of furniture has been hand picked with your comfort in mind.  When you walk in, you will know you've found your oasis in the city.  Clean, bright, calming tones will help you settle in, breath deep and unwind.  Every detail has been considered.  Your own parking place a few feet from the front door with just one step up makes this an especially easy choice for folks who hate wrestling luggage across parking lots and up stair cases.  A Dwell Magazine modern feel throughout will have you feeling like a celebrity every time you walk thro

neighborhood_overview: This ideal location yields very easy access to I-5, 8-10 minutes from downtown Seattle and 5 miles from The University of Washington and Children's Hospital.  Nestled in NE Seattle this location is just a few minutes drive from Greenlake, Cowen and Revenna parks.  The newly renovated and upscale North Gate Mall and Theaters are a 5 minute drive if you need to get out of the rain.  In addition, it is within walking distance of shopping/restaurants, less than 2 miles from Whole Foods Market and a short drive to access SR- 520 and I-90 to the east side.   Whether you're headed North, South, East or West, Mapleleaf is one of the most convienent jumping off points to experience Seattle and surrounding cities.   Here are some of the neighborhood businesses within a few blocks walking distance: - Cafe Piccolo (Italian restaurant) - Judy Fu's Snappy Dragon (Chinese restaurant) - Blue Saucer Coffee Shop (Stumptown Coffee) - Cloud City Coffee (Coffee, pastries/bakery, lunch) - Maple Leaf Grill (
notes: 2 other things... 1.  Most of our reviews are for the apartment before the 2018 remodel.  Just keep that in mind.  It's a completely different place now.   2.  There is a 2 chair, micro Hair Salon that operates above the apartment space daily from 9-9.  Sound has rarely been a problem but if you are especially sensitive this may be something to be aware of when considering our listing.  If on the other hand, you'd like to get pampered during your stay with us consider booking a cut, color or special night blow out with one of our wonderful stylists... it sure beats getting ready on your own :-)  Check us (Email hidden by Airbnb)
transit: The unit comes with it's own single parking space 5 feet from the front door and there is plenty of free street parking within a block or two if you need space for an extra car or two.  We are one block away from a metro bus stop that can take you or connect you to anywhere in the city.   Your return trip drops off literally across the street.
access: This listing refers to the entire Mother In Law apartment (the bottom level of the home).  It is completely private with it's own parking place, entrance, kitchen, bathroom, and laundry unit.
interaction: We do not live on the property, however we do have a property manager who lives upstairs and we are available via email or phone if you need anything during your stay!
host_about: We're a former Seattle couple who just couldn't bring ourselves to let go of our beautiful home.  We know Seattle, we love Seattle, we grew up here.  We just couldn't take the rain and traffic year round anymore.  What to do?  Turn it into an AirBNB dream of course!  For nearly a decade now we've been staying at our house when we're in town and when we're away.... we love to share it with the AirBNB Community.  Comfort, communication and kindness are our highest values.  We really care about what we are doing here.  We don't run multiple places. We're always available via phone or email even when we're traveling but most of the time, our house manager Kevin keeps everything on track.   This is our beloved home.  Our neighborhood.  Our memories.  We love hosting guests.  We love helping travelers make special memories of their own in our Seattle home. When we travel we prefer our hosts to be avilable if needed but otherwise not be around much which is how we run our place.  Our main motto in life is "Love others as you'd want to be loved.  To treat others as we'd want to be treated"

space: A cozy cottage behind a lovely Victorian house with separate access and a 3/4 (meaning shower but no bathtub) bathroom. The cottage has a brick patio and a large trellis on the south side covered with roses, grape vines, and wisteria and is surrounded by an English Garden. The pictures posted should give you the right idea.  (Alternative accommodation: We also have a really lovely rental space in the main house. See:  https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/20928 ) The cottage: there is a microwave, a small fridge, and an electric kettle for making coffee or tea. It offers considerable privacy if that is desired. The bed is queen-sized. Extra high-speed WiFi is also provided along with cable TV, including all of the premium channels. It is also possible to close some giant wood-paneled pocket doors if you want to divide the studio into a bedroom and sitting room, if case someone wants to sleep and someone else does not. neighborhood_overview: Ballard is a fantastic destination neighborhood for restaurants and bars and music. We are an easy walk (5-10 minutes) from downtown Ballard. Great breakfast places even closer.
notes: Golden Gardens Park on Puget Sound is a mile away and offers beautiful sunsets over the Olympic Mountains. The Ballard Locks are only a 5 minute walk and offer salmon ladder viewing and boats and a botanical garden worth the trip.
transit: Convenient and frequent bus service to downtown Seattle and to the U District.
access: Separate access for guest to come and go to and from the cottage up the "stairway to heaven" at the end of the driveway. Entrance is on the garden patio under the grape trellis. There is plenty of free parking on the street.
interaction: We are usually quite chatty with guests when they want to get acquainted. But it varies with the weather and our schedule and the degree of privacy our guests desire. But we always make contact early on and provide guidance to amenities in Ballard.
house_rules: The cottage only accomodates 2 people - there is one queen-sized futon that sleeps two, but is at least as comfortable as a regular box-spring bed. Smoking is allowed on the patio. Since recreational  marijuana is now legal in Washington State, we are totally cool with folks smoking it on our property. Sorry, no animals.  Also the studio-parts cannot be made child-proof, so we are not able to host small children or toddlers than might injure themselves. We do not offer breakfast as we have day jobs. But if visitors on the weekend are keen for breakfast (or some other meal or tea in the garden or whatever) on the premises, let us know and arrangments can be made. But there are plenty of great options nearby for breakfast.

space: A light-filled condo with beautiful hardwood floors, granite counters, stainless appliances and an interior that has been professionally designed for your comfort awaits! A fully-equipped kitchen gives you plenty of opportunity to make meals in, if you choose. Sit on your balcony and enjoy the Peekaboo view of the Elliott Bay, or go up to the rooftop deck for the expansive view of the Puget Sound! Free Wi-Fi is available in both the lobby and the rooftop deck as well as in the unit itself.

neighborhood_overview: Located just north of Seattle's downtown, this condo sits in the lively neighborhood of Belltown. There are restaurants on every block, bars to grab a drink, shops to explore, and did we mention the food? More than 63 eateries call Belltown home, and many are on our "don't miss" list. Since Belltown is residential, it is a perfect spot for guests of all ages.
notes: To be clear, this building does NOT have air conditioning (almost NO buildings-less than 5%- in Seattle have central air conditioning).  Also, be aware that this is a urban environment. In any urban core, you can expect to hear street noise, often late into the evening. If a silent outdoor environment is important to you, downtown Seattle (or any big city for that matter) may not be the best place for you to stay. That being said, this unit in the heart of Seattle--walkable to all the best Seattle has to offer-- and has high quality, noise muffling windows and heavy duty construction. Any questions about this, ask!
transit: Eight blocks to Pike Place Market; 7 blocks to the Space Needle; 5 blocks to the waterfront. Almost everything in downtown is within walking distance! If public transport is more your style, the building sits on a major bus thoroughfare that will take you beyond downtown. Or, you can call Lyft or a taxi any time!
access: Guest has full access to the condominium, as well as the building amenities: fitness center, a game room, pool table, and the incredible 3,000 square foot rooftop deck with amazing city views, multiple barbecues, fire pit, and lounge seating. host_about: This endeavor started when Darik and Sally purchased a condo in Belltown to use as a second home in the winter of 2007.Because of our nack at hosting, great marketing, amazing design, what was just an investment, has become a full-time business.  We currently have 48 properties in the heart of Downtown Seattle that we either own or manage on the behalf of others that have second homes in Downtown Seattle.Sally is an interior designer by trade, and I'm sure you'll be able to tell when it comes to the quality items to help you feel comfortable while you are staying with us.We take our position as hosts very seriously.  Our condos are cleaned immaculately and have the best staff in the business.  We are both foodies, and welcome the ability to share with you the best places in the city!Thanks, and we look forward to hosting you!

neighborhood_overview: LOCATION LOCATION LOCATION. With a walk score of 98 our home is just steps away from vibrant Capitol Hill's Broadway District, shops, restaurants, bars, theaters, but you'd never know it from the wonderfully quiet residential street. Capitol Hill is a vibrant community with a number of different business districts, each with their own charms and within easy walking distance. The flagship QFC Grocery Store is just a block away, plus there's a farmer's market on the weekends and just a bit farther the excellent Central Co-op. Both Broadway (1 block away) and John (2 blocks away) are major transit corridors, making getting around via transit very easy from the apartment. You also have easy access to the Broadway Streetcar and the Sound Transit Light Rail. Best of all, it's just a short and enjoyable walk to downtown Seattle, the Convention Center, Pike Place Market, the Seattle Waterfront, Volunteer Park and First Hill. Our Walkscore is 98, which means you should be able to walk to just a
notes: We can provide a parking permit that you hang in your car and park anywhere in the vicinity (Broadway not included). The parking permit (for residential parking only) is available upon request with a cash deposit of $80 (fully refundable upon return of permit). Otherwise there are some parking lots near by that do charge fees. Make sure to check posted signs. Parking can be difficult in our area especially during nights, weekends and during special events.  *Ceiling height is approx. 6.4" (193 cm) No Animals (even service animals)  This is a Smoke free and Animal free Residence!!

The neighborhood is filled with an array of excellent restaurants, boutiques as well as coffee houses. Walking distance from the major attractions such as Pike Place Market, Space Needle, Volunteer Park, Swedish medical center, South Lake Union, Cal Anderson Park, The Convention Center and Amazon.   Parking is not included in the rate.

notes: BOOKING PREFERENCES: **Please inquire about availability before sending reservation requests for stays of less than 5 nights during the summer. 4 nights otherwise.    We can sometimes accommodate shorter stays when they fit neatly between other reservations.  But, we try to avoid breaking up the calendar with short stays. Higher rates may apply for memorial day, 4th of july, labor day, and UW graduation, thanksgiving, christmas, NYE. We do not host events or gatherings. We own 3 other similar homes less than half a mile apart. Book all 3 for larger travel groups.
transit: There is 1 reserved off-street spot.  Uber and Car2Go are cheap and plentiful.  Car not required.  Walkscore of ~90.  Close to multiple bus routes.  Street parking is available, but observe parking signs.  32 bus (downtown) is 3 blocks away.  16 bus is 6 blocks away Driving times (without traffic) 4 minutes - Green Lake 7 minutes - University of Washington 7 minutes - Amazon South Lake Union 11 minutes - Quest Field - Go Hawks! 12 minutes - Space Needle 13 minutes - downtown Amtrak 25 minutes - Sea-tac Airport 28 minutes - Redmond Microsoft Campus 28 minutes - Bellevue 16 minutes - Seattle Children's Main campus 12 minutes - Fred Hutchinson
access: the whole home, to yourself.  There is a digital keypad so you can let yourself in at any time.
interaction: I live in the neighborhood and am always just a phone call, text, e-mail away.

host_about: I'm a global traveler with an appreciation for architectural details and delicious street foods.   I've had the good fortune of being one of the first hosts in Seattle, starting in 2009 and have been improving and growing my business ever since.   If you're considering coming as a guest without a full itinerary, I can give you the local scoop on a lot of great activities that you won't read about online or in your guide books.  Or, if you know the area or have it all figured, just let yourself into the home and enjoy our stay.As a guest, I know that Hosts make the best guests since we treat homes as if they were our own and take extra care to return everything as it was found.When I'm not hosting, I might be out running, rowing (seattle), cycling, or wearing down the tread on my hiking boots.  Either that, or perched on a neighborhood barstool catching up with the gang.

host_about: I describe myself as well travelled, trilingual, Italian my native language where I was born and raised, Spanish and some knowledge of French. ******Ethics, Loyalty and Integrity is how I live and work.  I have a solution oriented approach to everything in life. ******BA in Hospitality Management - have been in the Hospitality Industry, Customer service for almost 3 decadesMy sphere of clients has been very vast from simple people to Celebrities and Global.******Ten years as an International Travel Consultant.13 years as a Restaurateur - Botticelli Caffe, in Seattle where I designed, owned, operated and setting a higher standard in the food industry by introducing quality. In return I received Local and National recognition and created a non stoppable trend, ‰ÛÏPANINI‰Û. Receiving countless awards & reviews from elite organizations such as: Zagat, Travel and Leisure, The London Times, Travelhost, The New York Times, National Geographic Traveler, Seattle Best Places, Northwest Palate and all local publications.‰Û¢8 Years as a Realtor, Manager and Broker‰Ûªs Assistant - ethical position of trust, confidentiality & professionalism. Involved In the most stressful transaction of  people‰Ûª s lives, the purchase or sale of their most valued possession, their home. I am an entrepreneur and constantly evolving and reinventing myself, currently working on some projects  (Website hidden by Airbnb) and willing to share part of my house,  ‰ÛÏYour own apartment‰Û  and the warm hospitality to make your stay more enjoyable then a Hotel stay.Look forward to have you as a guest.Warm Regards, Pina ******CHARACTER REFERENCES:  ‰ÛÏI have known Pina for 18 years since I first moved to Seattle, when she owned and operated Botticelli Caffe. As a frequent customer I was able to watch Pina run both the cafÌ© and another Restaurant over the years. Pina was a tireless worker, sharing her time between the cafÌ©, her daughter and all of her many friends made through the business.  The clientele was made up of regulars who came in for her great smile and great conversation. Tourists were always given sound advice and direct ions to all of the best Seattle sites.I was able to work again with Pina on the purchase of my home where she was instrumental in finding the house my family enjoyed for several years along with all the close friends and neighbors Pina was able to introduce during our residence. Pina is always cheerful, dependable and tirelessly working to help those close to her.‰Û   (Website hidden by Airbnb) S.B. - Interior Designer ******I was a tenant in an apartment building that Pina managed. From inquiring about the apartment, to leasing and maintenance, Pina proved herself to be friendly, responsive, and available. My husband and I felt comfortable and well supported while the building was under Pina's management. When a new manager started, there was an unfortunate and noticeable change in the sense of community within the building. After experiencing many other apartment managers, I rate Pina as tops. She was always professional, reasonable, and neighborly. I would be lucky to find another manager as caring as Pina.B.S. - Transportation Consultant******‰ÛÏI have known Pina  for 15 years as a wonderful friend, reliable apartment manager, prosperous business owner, a professional Realtor and a wonderfully committed mother.I'm in senior product management at Microsoft, and if I want to make clear that Pina rates highly in all areas in my opinion - interpersonal communications skills, her attention to detail, her ability to socialize or work in a group in a charismatic and professional yet relaxed manner. She would be an asset to many and scores highly in my opinion‰Û R.R. - Consultant, Senior Product Management Microsoft******‰ÛÏPina was my agent and she did a fantastic job. She was professional, knowledgeable, patient, and persistent throughout the process.  I would definitely recommend her to anyone I know buying or selling their property.‰Û B. K.  Attorney at Law

neighborhood_overview: West Seattle is artsy and eclectic. It‰Ûªs a place that balances the richness of city living with the natural splendors of parks, beaches, and spectacular coastline views. It‰Ûªs a vibrant place with local clubs, live theater, and seasonal festivals. And many favorite cuisine choices are available throughout the area. Stroll on the beach, hike through Schmitz Reserve and Lincoln Park, or meander through vendor stalls at the Sunday Market. West Seattle is full of captivating beauty, and within easy access of dynamic downtown Seattle, and enticing sites in all directions.

name: Spacious Private Daylight Basement
summary: Large space with two bedrooms, a full bath with shower/jacuzzi tub, and a main room with a sectional couch, cable TV and laundry facilities. Private entrance from the backyard. Close to anything you might need. Quiet and comfy.
space: Peaceful place. We are a married couple--meditators, vegetarian, earth-friendly. We have a sweet black lab named Beloved Maria who may join you in the backyard garden or greenhouse if you take your coffee out there. The basement space is roomy but cozy; there is a lot of room to spread out and relax. The ceiling is a little low, so if you are over 6 feet tall, you will have to duck under the beams. You will have the entire space to yourselves--about 800 square feet. And there's a jacuzzi tub!

neighborhood_overview: We are right in the middle where the Greenwood, Greenlake, Ballard and Phinney Ridge neighborhoods meet.  Fantastic assortment of places to eat all within walking distance: Thai, Italian, Greek, Mexican, coffee shops--upscale, casual. Within one or two blocks: public library, post office, yoga studio, bus stop, bookstore, grocery store, health spa, and a Tibetan temple that offers free meditation sessions.  We are a 10-minute walk from Green Lake and on the bus line to downtown Seattle.  "Lucky Dog Clothing" - Premium Men's thrift store is located in the front of our home on the Greenwood side. Feel free to check them out they have amazing deals.
notes: We are positive, outgoing folks who love meditation, chanting, traveling, hiking, reading, and enjoy every moment. We're excited to meet you and provide a relaxing, comfortable place to stay.
transit: The express bus line downtown is one block away. Easy to walk to many places, including Green Lake.
access: Entire basement, backyard and greenhouse. It's fine to use the full kitchen upstairs as long as not cooking meat.
interaction: We want to make sure you are comfortable, and answer any questions about the neighborhood, the city or the region. Don't be shy!
house_rules: We both work during the week, so please  be considerate from 11:00 pm to 6:00 am. Please no meat cooked in the microwave downstairs.  No smoking. No pets.
host_about: Visala Hohlbein, 51 years old,  teach 5th grade in Seattle. Married to Dave, an editor, your co-host, for 28 years. Have 4 grown children. Love  the earth, meditation, nature, love the outdoors, love life! We're casual, friendly, open people.

Enjoy the plush bed, the tempurpedic sleeper sofa, the convenience of the washer and dryer, and a full bathroom with a huge mirror for getting ready.

neighborhood_overview: Located just north of Seattle's downtown, this condo sits in the lively neighborhood of Belltown. There are restaurants on every block, bars to grab a drink, shops to explore, and did we mention the food? More than 63 eateries call Belltown home, and many are on our "don't miss" list. Since Belltown is residential, it is a perfect spot for guests of all ages.
notes: To be clear, this building does NOT have air conditioning (almost NO buildings-less than 5%- in Seattle have central air conditioning).  Also, be aware that this is a urban environment. In any urban core, you can expect to hear street noise, often late into the evening. If a silent outdoor environment is important to you, downtown Seattle (or any big city for that matter) may not be the best place for you to stay. That being said, this unit in the heart of Seattle--walkable to all the best Seattle has to offer-- and has high quality, noise muffling windows and heavy duty construction. Any questions about this, ask!
transit: Eight blocks to Pike Place Market; 7 blocks to the Space Needle; 5 blocks to the waterfront. Almost everything in downtown is within walking distance! If public transport is more your style, the building sits on a major bus thoroughfare that will take you beyond downtown. Or, you can call Lyft or a taxi any time!
access: Guest has full access to the condominium, as well as the building amenities: fitness center, a game room, pool table, and the incredible 3,000 square foot rooftop deck with amazing city views, multiple barbecues, fire pit, and lounge seating. To top it off, secure parking is included in the price of this condo! Please note that Seattle Oasis Vacation Rentals does not manage the building but rather only specific units within. We are not responsible for closures and/or maintenance of any common space amenities.
interaction: With a 24 hour emergency line, and a team member always ready to assist during business hours, we are always a phone call away. All check-ins are scheduled well before your arrival so we can be ready for your arrival. Guests receive email copies of their check-in instructions, and are asked to electronically sign a standard rental agreement. Our smartphone app keeps all your reservation information handy. Please take note, there are no additional charges or fees due for your reservation. Payment for your reservation will be processed through Airbnb only.
house_rules: - Due to insurance requirements, renter must be at least 25 years of age. - Quiet Hours are 10PM ‰ÛÒ 8AM. This is a residential building primarily owner occupied. Please keep voices, televisions, and radios at an acceptable level at all times. - NO SMOKING! There is no smoking in the unit or on the unit balcony, or on the rooftop deck.  Smoking is only permitted 25 feet from the front door of the building per Washington State Law.  Please respect this rule for the enjoyment of our future guests and neighbors in our building. Also, please note that the building abides by federally permitted substances, not state legislation. - Pack 'n Plays and high chairs are available for an additional fee. - Check-in is 4PM on arrival day; check-out is 11AM on departure day. -A STANDARD RENTAL AGREEMENT, which includes a copy of the building rules, must be completed by the reservation holder. As a requirement of the building's HOA, these documents are to be signed and submitted to our office prior your
host_about: This endeavor started when Darik and Sally purchased a condo in Belltown to use as a second home in the winter of 2007.Because of our nack at hosting, great marketing, amazing design, what was just an investment, has become a full-time business.  We currently have 48 properties in the heart of Downtown Seattle that we either own or manage on the behalf of others that have second homes in Downtown Seattle.Sally is an interior designer by trade, and I'm sure you'll be able to tell when it comes to the quality items to help you feel comfortable while you are staying with us.We take our position as hosts very seriously.  Our condos are cleaned immaculately and have the best staff in the business.  We are both foodies, and welcome the ability to share with you the best places in the city!Thanks, and we look forward to hosting you!

A new Beautyrest Mattress will help you have a restful sleep. transit: Yes, one block from the guestsuite is the #28 bus which takes you to downtown Seattle in 25 minutes. Another bus, five blocks away, takes one to the University of Washington and ultimately downtown.
access: Our guests have a completely private apartment. Parking is off-street and 10 feet from the private entrance, two steps down into the hallway, not suitable for wheelchairs.
interaction: As little or as much as the guests desire. Since they have a totally private apartment, many guests prefer to relax there. The hosts are always available to answer questions, help with problems or just chat with a cup of tea or a glass of wine.

host_about: Retired yet busier than ever with a part time job as a German Translator for (Website hidden by Airbnb) selling on Ebay and and taking care of our house with the help of my husband. Hobbies include travel, photography and writing, vintage jazz among other interests.Ever since I got involved and introduced the European Bed and Breakfast concept to the Northwest in 1981 I have also dedicated myself to the comfort and care of my guests from around the world. The smallest detail is not overlooked and I have so many returning happy guests. Stay here and judge for yourself!

neighborhood_overview: The lovely Wedgwood neighborhood is great for walking and the shops and cafes are nearby.  Parks on the lake include Magnuson and Matthews Beach. The Burke-Gilman Trail is  in the neighborhood and runs through most of Seattle. This is a safe and friendly neighborhood.
notes: We are proud of our organic gardens and like to share flowers and produce. Our Art Gallery is features local artists. In July there is a fine art and craft fair here in Wedgwood with music and good food.
transit: Metro Buses 65, 71 to downtown, UW and the University District are just two blocks away.  There are several on call car services and Seattle has a rental bike system.
access: We have an amusing circular kitchen where many an interesting conversation happens in the evening. We have an extensive original art gallery by Seattle artists.
interaction: I have a semi-detached apartment and give an introductory walk about. Then I can be contacted by cell/ texting if needed. I enjoy hearing the guests plans and stories and sharing one or two of mine.
house_rules: This a quiet peaceful house with friendly creative people about. Relax,enjoy the many sights, cultural events and scenic delights of beautiful Seattle, Sleep surrounded by peaceful trees. Stay a while and  read or study or finish up a project. Single occupancy preferred. Non-smoking home. Responsible and respectful use is our our motto. We recycle mindfully.

Just 20 minutes from the airport by car, and another 20 minutes to downtown, with convenient bus access.  I offer a light airy bedroom with a double bed and plenty of space for your things.  Bathroom is shared.
space: Co-housing is a very unique living arrangement.  We know our neighbors, and sometimes share meals and activities.  My house is a short walk down a lovely path from the parking lot.  It is at one end of the community and the view from both the bedroom and front windows is one of gardens.

name: Central quiet Capitol Hill condo
space: This one bedroom condo has a large open layout kitchen and living room with lots of room to lounge. Located in artsy progressive Capitol Hill, you'll be walking distance from downtown (though the walk back is up the hill!) and a block from neighborhood bars and restaurants.  This location can't be beat. You also have the advantage of being located on a quiet residential street with plenty of street parking. One block in the other direction, you have Seattle's oldest mansions as well as Volunteer Park which includes a watchtower with a 360 degree view of the city, a botanical garden/conservatory, an outdoor amphitheatre (Shakespeare festival and various music events all summer long) and the Seattle Asian Art Museum.  The bedroom has a queen size bed. The red sofa (a glorified futon really, and surprisingly comfortable) converts to either two single beds or pushed together, a king. There are two other couches that convert to beds as well - bringing you up to 6 beds total. Guests are welc

house_rules: Please no smoking in the unit or near the building, we have especially sensitive neighbors and building rules.
host_about: I'm equal parts Airbnb guest and host - as I think everyone suffering from a case of wanderlust ought to be. I've travelled extensively and feel most at home when I'm surrounded by mementos of both the city I live in as well as the many cities I've explored. My home and my neighborhood are filled with lots of art, delicious food and great coffee - just like the places I like to stay when I'm on the road myself. Top 5 cities so far:1. Belgrade2. Barcelona3. Budapest4. Gotenberg5. JakartaI tend towards places off the beaten path but with lots of local charm - and I bet that many of my guests and my fellow hosts are much the same.

name: 2Bdr Seattle Apt in Victorian Home
summary: This two bedroom apartment has the convenience of location and spacious living, kitchen, bedroom and outdoor spaces.  Entrance through a garden courtyard makes this a delight.  Its location will get you hooked on one of Seattle's best coffee shops.
space: This is a private 2 bedroom apartment with living room, full kitchen, full bathroom, and laundry room.  It is fully furnished with cable TV, wireless internet, washer/dryer, bedding/towels, toiletries, dishwasher, and garbage disposal. One bedroom has a queen bed and one bedroom has twin bunkbeds‰ÛÓ-sleeping up to four comfortably.  We are a family with 9, 6 and 3 year old sons that is bringing much joy into our life.  We usually rented this apartment for year long leases to college students/young professionals since we are a short 8 minute walk to the University of Washington campus, but we are looking for some airbnb visitors for Spring and Summer 2018.

The entrance to the apartment is right by the backyard courtyard with garden and patio.
neighborhood_overview: We love how easily accessible everything is.  We also appreciate our neighbors whom make living in the city a gift everyday.  There is nothing like hanging out in your front yard and chatting up with neighbors that pass-by.
notes: Please note: we charge the $50 cleaning fee for all stays. Parking is only street parking and we have one free parking pass for guests to use during stay. Email us with questions.  We would love to have you.
transit: We are about a mile from Green Lake, 1.5 miles to University Village shopping area, a block from a main bus line that gets downtown in 10 minutes, and a 5 minute walk to the best Saturday farmers market in town.
access: The entrance to the apartment is right by the backyard courtyard with garden and patio.  The apartment is the basement of our home.  The apartment is private, with private entrance.  We share the washer/dryer and are open to sharing our back deck which has the BBQ and some chairs and tables.
interaction: This will vary depending on the day of the week, time of day and activities we have planned.  Kids and nanny are home during the day.  Family together in evenings.
house_rules: No noise after 10 pm (neighbors prefer this).  No illegal drugs or activity. No pets. No smoking.  No commercial use. We offer a parking pass for one car to allow for street parking, right outside our home. The Parking pass is difficult to get and so if this is lost you will owe us $100.
host_about: We are a young working family who love walking to work and being outdoors playing with our 9 year old, 6 year old and 3 old sons.  We enjoy gardening in the summer (which you will benefit from likely if you stay) and BBQing on the back deck during the wonderful summer month's in the Pacific Northwest.  We love our neighborhood since you can walk to shops, restaurants, parks, and the University of Washington.

name: West Seattle: Admiral calm & quiet
summary: Our downstairs bedroom/bathroom is spacious and private, with faux wood-paneling and a bit of sunlight, and a sitting area. We're about 3/4 to 1 mile to Alki Beach and half a mile to the California/Admiral intersection of W. Seattle. Short-term stays best.
space: Welcome to West Seattle! We've got a great guest room/shower bathroom combo with private patio entrance and street parking to share. While you are in our home, we stay upstairs and leave the daylight downstairs to you, more like you have an accessory unit than a room in the midst of the space we're using. The large room has 70s-style wood paneling, a comfy queen bed and sofa, flat-screen TV/DVD player, and a faux fire crackling in the (real) fireplace. People report sleeping well in our cool quarters.  We've been offline for the first part of 2013 while completing a re-landscaping project to install a new patio, outdoor lighting, walkways, and other hard-scaping at the house, with outdoor bench seating and a bar counter outside for a great outdoor room/picnic experience.  You'll find a coffee maker in the room and a fridge in the adjoining garage where you can chill snacks and drinks as you wish, but no real cooking facilities. name: Charming Apt, VERY Central Location
space: This open-plan one bedroom in a historic building is perfectly situated for a comfortable and convenient visit to Seattle. Ideally located between the Financial District and the Downtown Shopping District, you'll find yourself in a great spot no matter the purpose of your visit. The apartment is a three block walk from the nearest Light Rail Station, making for simple transportation to and from Sea-Tac Airport. All the major Downtown attractions - Pike Place Market, Seattle Art Museum, Benaroya Hall, Pioneer Square, 5th Avenue Theater and many more - are within an easy 10 minute stroll, as are numerous pubs, bars and restaurants. The apartment features high ceilings, classic moldings, bay windows and hardwood floors. Wireless internet, digital cable and a landline phone are all available for use during your stay. The building is secure with a controlled entry. The apartment is furnished to be comfortable and appealing, yours to make the most of during your sojourn to Seattle.

name: Haller Lake Restored Log Cabin
summary: Our little log cabin is back in action! We are back in the main house after living in the cabin for a year: a fun adventure!  About the cabin, it's mostly heated by the wood fireplace. Kitchenette has microwave, 1 burner, mini-fridge, dishes etc. upstairs is full-sized bed
space: Sweet restored stockade style log cabin right on Haller Lake. You would never know you were within the Seattle city limits! Haller Lake is a quiet, natural spring fed 15 acre lake surrounded by private homes.  Custom woodwork inside with artful touches. Sleeps 2 upstairs in full sized bed. Main floor has comfy sofa, kitchenette with microwave, single induction burner cooktop, coffee maker, toaster and small refrigerator, teapot, dishes and glasses; 3/4 bath with new stone tile shower. This cabin is heated mainly with the wood fireplace. The photos show the old wood stove. You can now watch the flames and there is a fan to spread the heat around a little better. There is also a deLonghi oil heater to add a little more heat when needed.  There is no TV but there is WiFi. Bring slippers, the stone floor gets chilly. Fish from the dock or take a ride in the paddleboat. We just got a canoe! (The boats are out of the water in the winter). No pets please! We are now living in the main house.
