neighborhood_overview: Much like New York City, Seattle is a city of neighborhoods, each with its own distinct personality. We live in Ballard, which has been called "the most soulful" neighborhood in Seattle. We think of it as the 21st arrondissement of Paris: the Farmers Market, the boutiques, the little coffee bars and boÌ¨tes. Our house is located one mile north of historic Ballard, close enough for a leisurely walk through this quaint, friendly neighborhood, and yet, far enough away to park easily and sleep undisturbed from others coming and going from all of the wonderful restaurants and bars this neighborhood has to offer! More info about Ballard:  + a 5-minute drive from Golden Gardens beach (with amazing sunset views of Elliot Bay and the Olympic Mountains) + a 20-minute drive from downtown (or, a 30-minute bus ride if you'd prefer to avoid the expense of parking) + a charming neighborhood, home to dozens of quaint boutiques, coffee shops, restaurants featuring many different types of cuisines (Frenc
notes: Guests who are staying 4 nights or more are invited to use our laundry facilities free of charge; however, we ask that you limit your laundry use to 2 loads per week. Short term guests (1-2 nights) who need to use the laundry facilities can do so at a charge of $3 per load. Please don't start any laundry before 10:30 p.m. We are happy to share the back deck and back yard common areas with our guests. We also have a secured garage if you need to store a bike or two. Guests who stay with us should be comfortable using stairs. There are 4 stairs up to the guest entrance, and 10 stairs down to the basement apartment.
transit: Old Ballard, the historic neighborhood is nearby our house, only a 15-20 walk, or a 5-minute drive away, so the vibrant night-life is nearby even though our house is located in a quiet neighborhood. Public Transport:  + Our house is located 3 blocks away from the bus to downtown Seattle in 20-30 minutes (on the #15,  or RapidRide D lines) - schedules can be found here on the Metro King County site. Bus rides to downtown will cost either $2.25 or $2.50 depending on whether you're riding at peak times. You can pay with cash (exact change since buses don't provide change back), or you can purchase an ORCA card that you can load with funds electronically. + From the airport, SeaTac, you can take the Link Light Rail for about $2.75 and 40-minute ride to Westlake Center in downtown Seattle. We recommend a cab from there, as it will only be about $10 and a bit easier than the city bus if you have luggage. If you choose to take a cab or Uber car directly from the airport, then you should expec
access: The basement level has a separate access and includes all of the necessities needed for a comfortable stay; however, guests are welcome to share any of the following features of our home with us:  + Large, private, fenced back yard with outdoor dining, large back deck, lounge chairs, and two-person hammock in case you would like to relax outside.  + Guests who stay 4 or more days are welcome to use laundry facilities for two free loads of laundry per week. Additional loads are available at a fee of $3 per load.
interaction: Interaction with Guests Tom is a Seattle-area native, and Corinne has lived in Seattle for 21 years, so if you are looking for recommendations, we're happy to provide local tips and advice. We have lived in the Ballard neighborhood for 9 years and have compiled a list of our favorite local restaurants, music venues, outdoor activities - most of which are located within a mile of our home.  We both have traveled quite a bit and are also big fans of being AirBnB guests ourselves because we enjoy having the opportunity to chat with other travelers. However, if guests are too busy having fun to chat, or would prefer more privacy, our guest facilities will be a great choice since the guest bedroom, bathroom and kitchenette are on a separate floor from our main living space; furthermore, the stairs between the two floors are separated by a door, so if you're not a fan of dogs, you don't have to worry about one of our dogs intruding in your space. Guests also have a separate entry to enter th
house_rules: We do not allow smoking indoors; however, there is a fenced yard and a covered front porch where people can smoke.  Check out time is set at noon to get ready for incoming guests. Most of the time we can work something out if you need a late check out, but check with us first to be sure we don't have anyone coming that afternoon. Please:  - Be kind to the apartment - we charge a very low cleaning fee for your benefit, so please reciprocate :) - Quiet time 11 pm - 7 am, but you can come and go as you please. We live above the apartment, but won't hear you as long as don't yell or don't blast the TV volume.  - All guests on the property must be registered with the Airbnb reservation. Any additional guests must be approved by host via email or text message. - Be sure to close and lock the back gate behind you to ensure security and safety of the property and our dogs) - Anyone on the property must abide by all local/state/federal laws (including alcohol, drug, and internet use). - No fire
host_about: Hello!We are avid Airbnb guests as well as hosts. We first stayed at an Airbnb location in Sydney, Australia, while honeymooning in January 2012, and were so impressed with our experience that we are now hooked! Not only are the Airbnb properties a good value, but more importantly, we have had amazing interactions with each of the hosts at locations where we've stayed, which now have expanded beyond Sydney, AU, to include a few locations in our home state of Washington as well as cities such as Paris, France, Vancouver, Canada, England: London, Cornwall and Bath, Oregon: Portland, Seaside, and Bend, California: San Francisco, Sebastopol, Petaluma, Willits, Palm Springs, and Sonora, New York: Williamsburg and Ithaca, Baltimore, Philadelphia, and Miami. We've been a guest in 41 different Airbnb listings over the past 6 years. In fact, I can't remember the last time we stayed at a conventional hotel!Since we had such great experiences as guests, we decided to start hosting in the summer of 2012 and listed our guest room on Airbnb. Hosting has proven to be a fantastic experience since we are both seasoned travelers and enjoy chatting with others about their travels, etc.In terms of demographics, we are both in our mid-forties, have traveled all around the country (and the world) and are also are very tidy and respectful. Beyond travelling, we like listening to live music, exploring neighborhoods, having fun with our dogs, gardening and cooking great food, spending time near the water/beach, and meeting new people.

host_location: and Seattle Washington and Montezuma,Costa Rica
host_about: HiOur names are Glen and Rose Marie we are a retired couple from Seattle.  We have a home in Montezuma and have lived the "pura vida" 6 to 7 months in Costa Rica every year since 2007.  We also love the north west US and have our home of 28 years  in Seattle in the Fremont neighborhood and  a duplex  in the Ballard neighborhood as well as well as a townhouse in the James Bay neighborhood of Victoria, BC which we just cannot give up so we have  turned them  into vacation rentals so we can enjoy them when we are around.   Since  we have vacation rentals you can be assured that we will  treat your place with respect and leave it in clean condition.  I love to garden, cook, travel, getting to know interesting people form all over the world,  and also enjoying  the beauty of the places were we live!  Hope you will enjoy our homes as much as we do!

name: Gluten Free on Phinney Ridge
summary: This cozy room is in a classic Craftsman home in a friendly, walkable neighborhood with easy access to downtown and other attractions via car or bus.  We provide breakfast foods (even gluten/dairy free) & kitchen access. Winter pricing special!
space: You'll sleep in a fun bedroom full of custom-painted murals and stars on the ceiling.  The bed is an antique 3/4 bed that may not be comfortable for two larger people, but is fine for most couples and perfect for a single.  Your private bath includes a clawfoot tub with shower.    This bedroom and bathroom are separated from the main floor living spaces (living/dining room) by a door, so you will have privacy. Families welcome.  An infant or toddler could sleep in a travel crib or "nest" on the floor. If your group needs more space, please see our listing for "Family Friendly on Phinney Ridge" for photos of our larger suite.

neighborhood_overview: Phinney Ridge is a great close-in neighborhood with a choice of restaurants and bars, featuring a monthly art walk.  Nearby shops include a local grocery, a card and gift shop, an independent bookstore, and the Space Travel Supply Store & Bureau of Fearless Ideas.  Woodland Park Zoo and Green Lake are within easy walking distance.  The Phinney Neighborhood Center is right up the street, offering an art gallery, concerts, a summer farmers market on Friday from 3:30-7:30 and other events.
notes: On request, we will prepare a gluten-free breakfast, including something baked.  We can also provide a listing of nearby restaurants and bakeries offering gluten-free menu items.  If you don't require a GF diet, we will provide choices of cereal, toast, yogurt, and fruit for you to fix your own conventional breakfast and there are many coffee shops and a great neighborhood grocery nearby.   We are a pet-free household, but there is a visiting neighborhood cat so it may not be a good fit if you are severely allergic.  Occasionally there may be family or Airbnb guests sleeping in a bedroom immediately below your space, although we try to avoid scheduling this way.  You may hear the next-door neighbors coming and going, as the bedroom window faces their driveway.  This is our home and we will welcome you personally. Because of our work schedules, we primarily accept guests who are able to arrive on Saturday or Sunday or between 6 and 9 pm on weeknights. We may have plans that requires us
transit: We're just a few blocks from the #5 bus, which takes you close to downtown museums, waterfront, shopping, etc., the Seattle Center (EMP, Science Center, ballet, festivals), or the funky Fremont neighborhood and only a transfer away from the University of Washington or Ballard, another up-and-coming neighborhood.
access: While visiting, you are welcome to share the living room, dining room, kitchen and deck of our Craftsman house with us.  We ask that you are aware and respectful of our use of the space as well.  We'll give you the wifi code when you arrive.
interaction: We are early risers (often before 6, but quietly) and appreciate quiet after 11 pm.  We will be in and out and preparing and eating our own meals at home during your stay.  We enjoy chatting in the kitchen and often check in via notes on the countertop.  We're happy to share recommendations, directions or other Seattle information.
house_rules: Arrivals must be coordinated with our schedule and are preferred before 9 pm.  Please communicate any arrival delays promptly.   We ask that guests come and go quietly after 11 pm.  Be sure to close and latch windows and lock front and back doors each time you leave the house. No fragrance sprays, strong perfumes, or other scented products in our home.  No smoking of any kind indoors or outdoors at our house. Top floor and rooms with closed doors are private.   Please ask if you want to ask other friends or family members to spend time with you while staying in our home.  No additional overnight guests. We appreciate it if guests leave their shoes in our foyer - both for cleanliness and also so that we can easily see if you are in for the evening, etc. and can be quiet for you or leave on the porch light, as needed. Wash any dishes you use - we don't have a dishwasher. Ask if you wish to do laundry.
host_about: We have lived in a great Seattle neighborhood for over 25 years and are married with 3 grown children.  Judith works at the University of Washington and enjoys dance, music, reading, and outdoor activities. We are active members of a Unitarian congregation.  Cal likes to go fishing when he's not at work.  We love to travel, but need to economize!

summary: This spacious suite is in a classic Craftsman home in a friendly, walkable neighborhood with easy access to downtown and other attractions via car or bus.  We provide breakfast foods (even gluten/dairy free) & kitchen access.  Although we have beds to accommodate 5 people (two doubles and a single), this space in our home is best suited to couples, families, or groups of 2-3 friends.  We are not a hostel, and have found that groups of 5 unrelated people are not the best fit for us.
space: This suite is on the ground floor and offers sleeping space for 2-5 people.  There is a bedroom with double bed and closet, a studio with single bed and counter space, and a den between them with a convertible double futon, which can accommodate two more people, as needed. Your private bath includes a stall shower but no tub.  DVD player only (no TV/cable access).  The studio offers space to spread out and work or get organized and a small TV for playing videos only (we have a selection for children).   If you require an additional bed and bath, you may also request our main floor listing, Gluten-Free on Phinney Ridge.  Access to your space is through our living area, down a short flight of stairs from our kitchen; it is not a private entrance. We are a pet-free household, but there is a visiting neighborhood cat so it may not be a good fit if you are severely allergic.

host_location: and Seattle Washington and Montezuma,Costa Rica
host_about: HiOur names are Glen and Rose Marie we are a retired couple from Seattle.  We have a home in Montezuma and have lived the "pura vida" 6 to 7 months in Costa Rica every year since 2007.  We also love the north west US and have our home of 28 years  in Seattle in the Fremont neighborhood and  a duplex  in the Ballard neighborhood as well as well as a townhouse in the James Bay neighborhood of Victoria, BC which we just cannot give up so we have  turned them  into vacation rentals so we can enjoy them when we are around.   Since  we have vacation rentals you can be assured that we will  treat your place with respect and leave it in clean condition.  I love to garden, cook, travel, getting to know interesting people form all over the world,  and also enjoying  the beauty of the places were we live!  Hope you will enjoy our homes as much as we do!

name: Serene Room in Sunny Cottage near Discovery Park
summary: This quiet room is a 1920's cottage home on a quiet street in the hip Seattle neighborhood of Magnolia. It is a short walk to Met Market & Discovery Park or the bus line.  This room has artistic furnishings and comfortable bed. This large private room while located in the basement is huge and feels secluded from the rest of the house. Downtown Seattle is a 10 minute drive away! And you are greeted by the sweetest pup in the world Jackx!     This room is great for a couple or a single traveler!
space: Private clean room in this artistic home.  It is located in the Magnolia neighborhood near Discovery Park!  The Serene room is located in the heated basement of the house.  There are many windows to draw open the shades & open the windows, that allow it to become light-filled! A Vintage armoire to house your items, with clean sheets and multiple pillows to rest your head!  The bed is super comfy, along with a full size desk! The bathroom on the main level of the house is shared, but it is perfect to shower with amenities such as shampoo & toothpaste, and a clean fluffy towel!   The cottage has a front deck that is basked in sunlight later in the day, and a back courtyard garden that is wonderful to sit and relish your coffee in the morning. Free high speed internet and wifi and on street parking too!! You are hosted by Cheryl the owner!! Enjoy the full comforts of home with the use of the kitchen, while being welcomed by my dog Jackx & my kitty Bobbin. We are one block from the biggest

neighborhood_overview: It does not feel as if you are in a big city. I love these restaurants in Magnolia: The Gim-Wah for chinese, Uptown for the best coffee Serendipity for the burgers, Starbucks for light heathly eats Pagliacci for Pizza Metropolitain Market for the Deli
notes: You can come and go as you need.
transit: Yes, a bus-stop (take either the #24 or #33) is a 1 min walk away! Across the street (south side of the street ) in front of the 76 gas station is the bus stop to go downtown. On the north side of the street is the stop to get off at to return.
access: Guests can use the kitchen until 9.30pm. Laundry is available for $5 a load, with detergent & dryer sheet provided.
interaction: I like to give the guests their space.  And they can come to me with any questions at any time. Sometimes we share a meal too  if it works for everyone!
house_rules: Please be respectful of house residents, property and animals. I appreciate all efforts to recycle and conserve on water and electricity. There is no smoking in this house or on the property. No hard drugs or pot smoking allowed. If you need something I would be delighted to see if I can accommodate you! Ask questions if you are not sure! I hope that you enjoy staying here as much as I love living here!! Quiet after 10pm.  Thank-you!
host_about: Sewing Pattern Designer & Instructor  I love fabric piles & gardening & the Pacific Northwest.  I hope you enjoy Seattle as it really is a great city!!I am happy to assist you with anything.  I work at home most of the time except when I travel to teach sewing on national & international levels. Be warned the Zoo (Jackx, the yellow lab & Bobbin, the kitty will greet you!!I hope you get a chance to discover Discovery Park, the largest park in Seattle where you can walk to the water or to the look-out over the bluff.  Pike's Place Market is not to be missed along with Seattle Art Museum, Gas Works Park, Kayaking in the Arboretum, & the chance to day-trip to small towns along the coast.Just remember that "Life" is what we choose to make of it!!

name: Sunny Parisian beauty room w/ comfy bed
summary: This classic beauty is decorated in simple black and white with soft accents for a calming stay, A soothing light filled space offers an old world touch of class.The room is furnished in turn of the century antique furniture and playful decorations. shared kitchen, huge bath, free wifi and parking all for you. space: Welcome to the Parisian beauty room!    This  room has been recently moved and renovated into a quieter and larger space. The new beauty room is now a softer color palette and soothing lay out is better for singles and couples (more space). The  renovation has created a more soothing , light filled space with all the old world charms.A clean and simple black and white with soft accents make this a calming and sensual oasis. This building has a long and wonderful history (built in 1904)  and has been renovated with this esthetic in mind. This is a single room with a  fantastic new plush full size bed with a pillow top for your comfort. Getting a good nights sleep helps your trip go well. I strive to make you comfortable so if you need something feel free to ask for it.  Our building offers comfortable rooms with lovely wood floors and wainscotting down the hallways. neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is so much fun and it has a unique flare. This neighborhood is very creative and burgeoning arts district but not for everyone,it's a slightly industrial area and gritty in interesting ways. It's very safe and usually lots of people on the street who are enjoying a myriad of restaurants in the area. Foodies love it here. You should be open and ready for a fun adventure if you want it. You do not have to be creative to stay here, just open to different types of people and experiences. We have lots of fun restaurants and fun things to do including a circus school and glass blowing studios. Bus is right across the street and goes directly to down town and the light link rail. Georgetown is hoppin come see it for yourself and read our reviewsIndustrial Arts district meets thriving commercial meets victorian era esthetics (URL HIDDEN) Geor(URL HIDDEN) A little grit,a lot of love and a burgeoning arts community. Easy 15 minute bus ride to Pike Place Market,the Big Wheel and
notes: Downstairs in our building we have a restaurant (Star Brass Lounge), a pool hall and a coffee shop and its just downstairs! whohooo! This neighborhood is fun and safe but on the weekends it can sometimes be festive . Its really very quiet 98% of the time but I just have to mention that depending on how the Seahawks are doing it may not be "quiet "
transit: Bus 124 is right across the street that goes right to downtown to light link rail and the airport. We also have an easily walkable neighborhood. If you need help with travel, transportion feel free to ask Here are instructions from the airport if you are using mass transit Yes you will get the link rail from the airport to the underground tunnel, get off in the international district, cross the tracks to go to bus number 106 going south to Georgetown. The bus will take about 15 minutes. You will get off in Georgtown at the Doris street stop. Call me from there , you will walk back towards city 1/2 block. Our building is located in the middle of the block. I am happy to answer any ?'s before and during your visit
access: We have three bathrooms, but the "Barry White bath" is reserved especially for AIR guests and is a tiled shower that is HUGE and it has 8 shower heads. Full kitchen is accesible. Building is 24/7 access with quiet hours from 10 pm -8am. You have free wifi  access. Professional Artist studios  surround your room so please be OK with creative people. It is a very calm space with professional artists who enjoy saying hello every once in a while but respect your space also. Please no non Airbnb guest allowed on premises
interaction: I honor guests requests promptly and try to gauge each guests needs , if you want allot of interaction I will happily show you around a little, pour you a glass of wine and chat or If you prefer being more solitary, I  will give you your tour and instructions and leave you  alone. Its really up to you. I am a hard working person so I wont take up your precious travel time but I am willing to share ideas on places to go, food suggestions and life in Seattle. I am not a hands off host unless you need me to be
house_rules: ‰Û¢ Check-in time should be confirmed before your arrival. Some late night arrivals may be okd but need to be arranged first. We have a night manager who may be able to accomodate you but greeting host in person is prefereed. Suggested arrival is between 3PM to 7 pm, please communicate late check ins before booking please as I may or may not be able to accommodate them Quiet hours from 10pm - 8am Please keep speaking/music /entertainment volume low so that the resident and other guests may enjoy their sleep or studio time. This is not a party place and non airbnb guests are not allowed unless arranged before hand, this helps keep things serene and safe. Thank you  This is space is an oasis of calm in the middle of the city and we look forward to your stay. Please No drugs, Light alcohol use is fine, no smoking or flame of any kind  inside,  Cooking in kitchen encouraged but please clean up after yourself and remember to cook quietly after 10 pm.  *Please no NON airbandb guests in bella u
host_about: I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a Non profit community  Arts and Cultural Center. I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs when needed (this includes you) spend time with friends and my dogs.  The guest rooms are located in the Centers lovely  1904 building and we share the building with professional artist studios (mine included). The building is truly a vintage charmer and I have been doing the renovations myself. I think you will enjoy my handy work. Special things to be aware of***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunatly are not ADA accesible. ***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a coffee shop that on the weekends sometimes has fun shows / music / drag shows/mystery theater..which is fun for most but light sleepers may not be ok with this activity.  I look forward to meeting you. I have two small calm Jack Russel's who may greet you but do not  stay in the space at night. I enjoy animals,art, gardening and people.. . This is not a hotel and I do not have staff so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) and communicate this BEFORE your arrival as I arrange my day around meeting you. Late arrivals may be possible with prior arrangement and may be handled by our night manager Rick. I am an easy going person band always try to keep our space mellow  NO SMOKING IN BUILDING / NO VAPING/ NO POT ‰Û_you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every visitor a friend but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dogs.I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I even have a lonely planet guide to Seattle if you want to borrow it.I cant wait to meet you!To earn more about our area (Georgetown) follow (copy and paste) this link (Website hidden by Airbnb) My life motto"Life is short, art is long"
